## 🔴 PROBLEM 1 — SIDEBAR ICONS ARE A RAINBOW DISASTER

**What's wrong:** The section icon containers have vivid, high-saturation color backgrounds (blue for Contact, purple for Summary, red for Experience, amber for Education, green for Skills, etc). When you stack 13 of them in a list, it creates a garish technicolor nightmare. This is the #1 reason the page "looks like shit". It looks like a children's app, not a professional resume tool.

**Root cause:** The `colorClass` prop on each section has `bg-blue-500/10`, `bg-purple-500/10` etc. These 10% opacity tints are still too strong and too varied.

**Fix — `EditorPage.tsx` (both desktop AND mobile sidebar, both `sectionGroups.map` blocks):**

**Step 1:** Remove all individual `colorClass` definitions from the `sectionGroups` array entirely. Replace every section's `colorClass` with a single unified neutral style:

```tsx
// DELETE the entire colorClass property from every section in sectionGroups.
// Before:
{ id: 'contact', title: 'Contact Info', icon: UserIcon, colorClass: 'bg-blue-500/10 text-blue-400 ...' }

// After — no colorClass needed at all:
{ id: 'contact' as const, title: 'Contact Info', icon: UserIcon }
{ id: 'summary' as const, title: 'Profile Summary', icon: FileTextIcon }
{ id: 'experience' as const, title: 'Work Experience', icon: BriefcaseIcon }
// ... etc, all without colorClass
```

**Step 2:** Update the icon container `div` to use a single neutral style:

```tsx
// Before (uses section.colorClass):
<div className={`w-10 h-10 rounded-2xl flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center transition-colors ${section.colorClass}`}>

// After (single neutral, icon gets accent color only on hover):
<div className="w-9 h-9 rounded-xl flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center bg-zinc-800/60 text-zinc-400 group-hover:text-zinc-200 group-hover:bg-zinc-700/60 transition-colors">
```

**Step 3:** The icon itself — keep it small `w-4 h-4` (not w-5 h-5, that was too big):
```tsx
<Icon className="w-4 h-4 transition-colors" />
```

